# {{appName}}

> AKARI Full Tier App — `{{appId}}`

## Overview

{{appName}} is a [Full Tier](https://github.com/akari-os/akari-os/docs/sdd/specs/spec-akari-app-sdk.md) AKARI app.
Full Tier apps provide a custom React panel and can define agents and expose skills.

## Requirements

- Node.js >= 18
- AKARI OS with SDK `{{sdkRange}}`

## Development

```bash
npm install
akari dev          # start dev server and mount into local Shell
```

## Certification

```bash
akari app certify   # run Automated Lint + Contract Tests (HUB-024 §6.8)
```

## Distribution

```bash
# Self-distribution (Automated Lint + Contract Test only)
npm publish

# AKARI Marketplace (requires Manual Review)
akari app publish
```

## Structure

```
{{appSlug}}/
├── akari.toml               App manifest (AKARI-HUB-024 §6.5)
├── src/
│   ├── index.ts             Entry: panel registration + skill registration
│   └── panel.tsx            Main React panel component
├── agents/
│   └── assistant.md         App agent spec (ADR-011)
├── skills/                  Exported skill implementations
└── tests/
    └── contract/            App Contract Tests (HUB-024 §6.8)
```

## Guidelines

- All state must go through Pool / AMP — no local DB (HUB-024 §6.7 rule 2)
- All AMP records must include `goal_ref` (HUB-024 §6.6 Memory API)
- Do not create independent windows — use Shell panel API only (rule 3)
- Declare only necessary permissions in `akari.toml` (rule 5)

